 <strong style="color:var(--amber);">June 29, 2025</strong> — First SOC 2 Type II report received. Gaps identified.<br>
 <strong style="color:var(--amber);">Sept 2025</strong> — Remediation underway. Ridhwan Chowdhury leading. 54 policies, VAPT, MFA, patch management.<br>
 <strong style="color:var(--amber);">Late 2025</strong> — Type I assessment requested by InfoIMAGE, then cancelled. Decision made to proceed directly to second Type II.<br>
 <strong style="color:var(--amber);">Jan 2026</strong> — Second SOC 2 Type II audit begins (covering full 2025 calendar year).<br>
 <strong style="color:var(--amber);">April 2026</strong> — Final SOC 2 Type II report received. our organization certified. ✓
 </p>
 </div>

 <div class="takeaway fade-up">
 <div class="callout-label">Take Away — Chapter 8</div>
 <ol>
 <li>our organization's SOC 2 journey was client-driven (InfoIMAGE) and took approximately 15 months from first engagement to clean Type II certification.</li>
 <li>The first report surfaced gaps — which is exactly what it's supposed to do. The real work was in the remediation phase that followed.</li>
